ed%20by%20a%20Hong%20Kong%20court%20to%20liquidate%20after%20two%20years%20in%20a%20debt%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20has%20appointed%20Alvarez%20and%20Marsal%20as%20liquidator%20to%20manage%20the%20company%2C%20Evergrande%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hkexnews.hk%2Flistedco%2Flistconews%2Fsehk%2F2024%2F0129%2F2024012900565.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20filing%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Hong%20Kong%20Stock%20Exchange.%20Alvarez%20and%20Marsal%20will%20now%20take%20control%20of%20Evergrande's%20assets%20and%20prepare%20to%20sell%20them%20in%20order%20to%20repay%20the%20real-estate%20developer's%20debts%2C%20which%20total%20%24300%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Beijing%20is%20unlikely%20to%20ensure%20that%20overseas%20investors%20get%20their%20money%20back%2C%20say%20analysts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20while%20Beijing%20wants%20to%20restore%20foreign%20investor%20confidence%20in%20China%2C%20authorities%20are%20probably%20not%20keen%20to%20start%20inflating%20the%20country's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcountry-garden-china-real-estate-problems-explainer-evergrande-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edebt-fuelled%20property%20bubble%3C%2Fa%3E%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Chinese%20leadership%20faces%20a%20delicate%20tradeoff%20between%20attracting%20foreign%20investment%20by%20maintaining%20credibility%20with%20investors%20versus%20holding%20the%20real-estate%20sector%20on%20a%20leash%2C%26quot%3B%20Emil%20M%C3%B8ller%2C%20the%20head%20of%20research%20at%20Steno%20Research%2C%20an%20independent%20Denmark-based%20research%20company%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstenoresearch.com%2Fwatch-series%2Fevergrande-nugget-popping-the-worlds-largest-asset-bubble%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereport%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20January%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20China%20wa