s%2C%20personnel%20taken%20through%20outsourcing%20agencies%2C%20executives%20from%20Public%20Sector%20Units%2C%20state-owned%20banks%20and%20regulatory%20bodies%20on%20loan%2C%20retired%20government%20employees%2C%20and%20those%20hired%20for%20housekeeping%2C%20multi-tasking%2C%20and%20data%20entry%20functions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20six%20departments%20with%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20consultants%20from%20external%20agencies%20are%20Health%20and%20Family%20Welfare%20(203)%2C%20Rural%20Development%20(166)%2C%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%20Welfare%20(149)%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Administration%20(147)%2C%20Women%20and%20Child%20Development%20(112)%20and%20Road%20Transport%20and%20Highway%20(99).%20All%20in%20all%2C%20they%20account%20for%20876%2C%20or%2058%25%2C%20of%20the%20total%201%2C499.%20Barring%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Welfare%2C%20which%20has%20not%20provided%20information%2C%20the%20annual%20expenditure%20of%20these%20departments%2F%20ministries%20on%20consultants%20from%20external%20agencies%20is%20Rs%20130%20crore%20(43%25%20of%20the%20total%20Rs%20302%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20regards%20the%20Young%20Professionals%2C%20NITI%20Aayog%20employs%20most%20of%20them%20at%2095%20individuals%20at%20present.%20Among%20independent%20consultants%20hired%20on%20contract%2C%20the%20top%20three%20are%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%20Welfare%20(86)%2C%20NITI%20(52)%2C%20and%20Road%20Transport%20and%20Highways%20(41).%20As%20for%20domain%20experts%20on%20contract%2C%20Agriculture%20and%20Farmers%20Welfare%20(92)%2C%20followed%20by%20Civil%20Aviation%20(70)%20and%20Rural%20Development%20(45).%20Each%20of%20these%20domain%20experts%20and%20independent%20consultants%20is%20paid%20anywhere%20between%20Rs%201%20lakh%20and%20Rs%204%20lakh%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20government%20abolishing%20Group%20D%20(peons%2C%20data%20entry%2C%20housekeeping%2C%20etc)%20recruitment%2C%20the%20personnel%20for%20such%20jobs%20is%20hired%20through%20outsourcing%20agencies%2C%20mostly%20through%20the%20government-run%20Government%20e-Marketplace%20(GEM)%20portal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20notable%20point%20here%20is%20that%20the%20Big%20Four%20accounting%20and%20consulting%20giants%20%E2%80%93%20Ernst%20%26amp%3B%20Young%2C%20PwC%2C%20Deloitte%2C%20and%20KPMG%20%E2%80%93%20secured%20projects%20worth%20nearly%20Rs%20450%20crore%20from%20the%20Union%20government%20between%202017%20and%202022.%20In%20the%20given%20period%2C%20together%20they%20bagged%20at%20least%20305%20consulting%20assignments%20worth%20nearly%20Rs%20500%20crore%20from%20various%20government%20ministries%20and%20departments%2C%20according%20to%20a%20previous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexpress-exclusive%2Fin-5-years-16-ministries-gave-rs-500-crore-work-to-big-five-consultants-9018061%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20bureaucrats%20have%20long%20decried%20the%20hiring%20of%20external%20consultants%20for%20government%20work.%20Writing%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fopinions%2F2023%2FNov%2F24%2Fconsultancy-raj-not-a-cure-for-all-government-ills-2635923.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20former%20Cabinet%20secretary%20K.M.%20Chandrashekar%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20tendency%20towards%20outsourcing%20regular%20government%20work%20to%20consultants%20will%20ultimately%20adversely%20affect%20the%20quality%20of%20administration.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20article%20titled%20%E2%80%98%3Cbdi%3EConsultancy%20Raj%20not%20a%20cure%20for%20all%20government%20ills%E2%80%99%2C%20%3C%2Fbdi%3EChandrashekar%20notes%20several%20worldwide%20consultancy%20errors%2C%20calling%20%E2%80%9Caccountability%20the%20biggest%20casualty%E2%80%9D%20in%20relying%20on%20external%20consultants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20problem%20with%20public%20administration%20in%20India%20is%20not%20a%20lack%20of%20knowledge%20or%20the%20unavailability%20of%20qualified%2C%20well-trained%20officers.%20Many%20Indian%20civil%20servants%20have%20achieved%20tremendous%20results%20in%20particular%20areas%2C%20where%20they%20have%20built%20enduring%20systems%20and%20institutions%2C%20and%20have%20qualifications%20as%20good%20as%20the%20best%20in%20corporate%20India.%20The%20challenge%2C%20really%2C%20is%20to%20build%20an%20overarching%20results-based%20system%20that%20takes%20into%20account%20the%20diversity%20of%20government%20work%20and%20is%20flexible%20enough%20to%20change%20according%20to%20need.%20This%20requires%20the%20collective%20effort%20of%20all%20ministries%2C%20departments%20and%20institutions.%20Consultancies%20can%20provide%20no%20shortcuts%20to%20paradise%E2%80%94the%20government%20has%20to%20bite%20the%20bullet%20and%20take%20responsibility%20for%20itself%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fopinions%2F2023%2FNov%2F24%2Fconsultancy-raj-not-a-cure-for-all-government-ills-2635923.html%5C%22%3Esums%20up%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706602512000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30133757%2FEffect-90.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-govts-reliance-on-consultants-nearly-1500-in-44-departments-are-annually-paid-rs-302-crore%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%2C%20however%2C%20does%20not%20include%201%2C037%20Young%20Professionals%2C%20539%20independent%20consultants%2C%20354%20domain%20experts%2C%201%2C481%20retired%20government%20officers%2C%20and%2020%2C376%20other%20low-paid%20staff%20hired%20on%20contract%20by%2076%20departments%20employed%20either%20directly%20or%20through%20outsourcing%20agencies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-govts-reliance-on-consultants-nearly-1500-in-44-departm