hart%20and%20her%20navigator%2C%20Fred%20Noonan%2C%20departed%20from%20Lae%2C%20New%20Guinea.%20They%20were%20heading%20for%20Howland%20Island%2C%20a%20small%20island%20located%20in%20the%20central%20Pacific%20Ocean%2C%20but%20they%20never%20arrived.%20By%201939%2C%20both%20Earhart%20and%20Noonan%20were%20declared%20dead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20case%20remains%20unresolved%2C%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcelebrity-conspiracy-theories-2017-5%5C%22%3Econspiracy%20theories%3C%2Fa%3E%20abound%20over%20the%20late%20pilot's%20fate.%20Here%20are%20five%20of%20the%20most%20compelling%20guesses%20behind%20what%20happened%20to%20Earhart's%20ill-fated%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1.%20Earhart%20crashed%20her%20plane%20and%20drowned%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222156%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22amelia%20earhart%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5af2f7b700c71c43008b45db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221617%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEarhart%20was%20declared%20legally%20dead%20on%20January%205%2C%201939.%3Cp%3EKeystone%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECrash-and-sink%20theorists%20postulate%20that%20Earhart%20ran%20out%20of%20fuel%20while%20trying%20to%20locate%20tiny%20Howard%20Island%20and%20subsequently%20crashed%20into%20the%20open%20ocean%20and%20drowned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20theory%20is%20supported%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20Earhart%20and%20Noonan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.uscg.mil%2FPortals%2F1%2Fevents%2Fpdf%2Fjuly.pdf%5C%22%3Eput%20in%20many%20calls%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20US%20Coast%20Guard%20ship%20%26quot%3BItasca%2C%26quot%3B%20communicating%20that%20they%20were%20low%20on%20fuel%20and%20having%20trouble%20finding%20Howard%20Island.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.biography.com%2Fpeople%2Famelia-earhart-9283280%5C%22%3E%244%20million%20rescue