20the%20Alt%C3%B3ir%20na%20Gr%C3%A9ine%20or%20sun%20altar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20stood%20for%20about%204%2C000%20years%20but%20disappeared%20by%201852%20when%20an%20antiquarian%20noted%20it%20had%20been%20dismantled%2C%20according%20to%20Irish%20broadcaster%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rte.ie%2Fnews%2Fmunster%2F2024%2F0118%2F1427170-lost-tomb-kerry%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERaidi%C3%B3%20Teilif%C3%ADs%20%C3%89ireann%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Its%20exact%20location%20was%20a%20mystery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20170%20years%20later%2C%20during%20COVID%20lockdowns%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efolklorist%20Billy%20Mag%20Fhloinn%20went%20searching%20for%20the%20temple's%20remains%20on%20a%20hill%20called%20Cruach%20Mh%C3%A1rthain%20near%20the%20village%20of%20An%20Buailt%C3%ADn.%20He%20found%20a%20few%20of%20the%20large%20stones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20interested%20in%20this%20particular%20tomb%2C%20firstly%20because%20it%20is%20less%20than%20half%20a%20mile%20from%20my%20house%20but%20also%20the%20mystery%20surrounding%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Mag%20Fhloinn%20told%20Business%20Insider%20via%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20structure%20may%20have%20once%20held%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-tomb-opened-pacopampa-peru-possible-religious-cult-leader-unearthed-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremains%20of%20Bronze%20Age%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20they%20may%20have%20used%20it%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbronze-age-cauldrons-show-evidence-what-ancient-feasts-looked-like-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eceremonies%20and%20rituals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Mag%20Fhloinn%20told%20RT%C3%89.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPhotographs%20helped%20find%20the%20site%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMag%20Fhloinn%20lives%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20Cruach%20Mh%C3%A1rthain%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehill%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Farchaeology%2Fremains-of-4000-year-old-lost-tomb-discovered-in-ireland%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELive%20Science%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20An%20instructor%20at%20Dingle%20campus%20of%20Connecticut-based%20Sacred%20Heart%20University%2C%20he's%20mapping%20the%20sites%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F20650866%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewedge%20tombs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20types%20of%20structures%20are%20burial%20places%2C%26quot%3B%20Mag%20Fhloinn%20said%2C%20generally%20dating%20to%20around%202%2C500%20to%202%2C000%20BCE.%20%26quot%3BThey%20contain%20the%20cremated%20remains%20of%20a%20number%20of%20different%20people%2C%20mixed%20together%20in%20the%20chamber.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bronze%20Age%20stone%20tombs%20are%20widespread%20and%20numerous%20across%20parts%20of%20Ireland.%20Many%20others%20have%20been%20excavated.%20Researchers%20have%20found%20pieces%20of%20pottery%2C%20remnants%20of%20fires%2C%20and%20other%20evidence%20that%20people%20may%20have%20performed%20rituals%20at%20similar%20tombs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20places%20of%20ceremony%2C%20and%20it%20might%20be%20useful%20to%20think%20of%20them%20as%20being%20like%20ancestor%20shrines%20as%20much%20as%20graves%2C%26quot%3B%20Mag%20Fhloinn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20searches%20of%20the%20hill%2C%20Mag%20Fhloinn%20took%20photographs%20to%20create%20a%203D%20model.%20Using%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneanderthal-oldest-cave-drawings-found-france-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etechnique%20known%20as%20photogrammetry%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20digitally%20joined%20different%20images%20together.%20That's%20when%20he%20noticed%20the%20orthostats%2C%20or%20upright%20stones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERotating%20the%203D%20model%20on%20his%20screen%2C%20Mag%20Fhloinn%20saw%20how%20well%20it%20corresponded%20with%20the%201838%20drawing.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20my%20real%20eureka%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20few%20left-behind%20stones%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMag%20Fhloinn%20and%20a%20fellow%20scholar%2C%20Se%C3%A1n%20Mac%20an%20tS%C3%ADthigh%2C%20printed%20out%20Chatterton's%20picture%2C%20went%20up%20to%20the%20site%2C%20and%20found%20two%20matching%20stones.%20%26quot%3BTwo%20stones%20matching%20was%20very%20solid%20evidence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20surprising%20find.%20Richard%20Hitchcock%2C%20the%20antiquarian%20who%2C%20in%201852%2C%20couldn't%20find%20the%20tomb%2C%20wrote%20that%20the%20stones%20had%20%26quot%3Bbeen%20broken%20and%20carried%20away%20for%20building%20purposes%2C%20as%20if%20there%20were%20no%20others%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%2C%26quot%3B%20RT%C3%89%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECaimin%20O'Brien%2C%20an%20archaeologist%20with%20the%20National%20Monuments%20Service%2C%20verified%20Mag%20Fhloinn's%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%20over%20180%20years%20archaeologists%20know%20where%20the%20tomb%20is%20situated%20and%20it%20will%20enhance%20our%20understanding%20of%20wedge-tomb%20distribution%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Brien%20told%20RT%C3%89.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20the%20lost%20tomb%20has%20been%20found%2C%20the%20archaeologists%20want%20to%20know%20if%20the%20sun%20altar%20lives%20up%20to%20its%20name.%20Some%20wedge%20tombs%20were%20built%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20wedge%20tombs%20face%20west%2C%20particularly%20to%20the%20southwest%2C%20Mag%20Fhloinn%20said.%20But%20this%20tomb%20seems%20to%20be%20pointing%20east.%20%26quot%3BLocal%20folklore%20talks%20about%20the%20rising%20sun%20casting%20light%20upon%20the%20stones%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20might%20make%20the%20tomb%20interesting%20to%20archaeoastonomers%2C%20he%20said%2C%20who%20could%20%26quot%3Bsee%20if%20there%20is%20any%20truth%20to%20the%20folk%20accounts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERe