20economic%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20must%20be%20emphasised%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%20on%20his%20own%20has%20often%20announced%20electorally%20sensitive%20and%20popular%20fiscal%20measures%20%E2%80%93%20including%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2F5-year-extension-to-pmgkay-an-acknowledgment-of-indias-nutrition-access-crisis%5C%22%3Eextension%20of%20schemes%20like%20PMGKAY%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20throughout%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20with%20a%20goal%20to%20target%20poor-centred%20welfarism%20in%20states%20going%20to%20the%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Union%20Budget%E2%80%99s%20overall%20macro-outlays%2C%20however%2C%20amidst%20a%20larger%20proportion%20announced%20for%20capital%20expenditure%20over%20the%20last%20few%20Union%20Budgets%2C%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthree-charts-what-really-matters-to-india-versus-what-parties-jockey-for-in-emotional-tug-to-voters-hearts%5C%22%3Ecoming%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20essential%20social%2Fwelfare%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthree-charts-what-really-matters-to-india-versus-what-parties-jockey-for-in-emotional-tug-to-voters-hearts%5C%22%3Ehas%20been%20repeatedly%20criticised%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20opposition%20for%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthree-charts-what-really-matters-to-india-versus-what-parties-jockey-for-in-emotional-tug-to-voters-hearts%5C%22%3Einability%20to%20fight%3C%2Fa%3E%20rising%20inflation%20and%20high%20youth%20unemployment.%20Rather%2C%20the%20government%20does%20everything%20in%20its%20power%20to%20not%20even%20let%20these%20issues%20be%20highlighted%20in%20any%20of%20the%20Budget%20speeches%20or%20organised%20deliberations%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsocial-policy-debates-aimed-at-making-the-govt-look-good-are-missing-clarity-and-reason%5C%22%3Ewith%20the%20support%20of%20government%20economists%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EManaging%20%E2%80%98vanishing%E2%80%99%20middle-class%20expectations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20author%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Feconomy%2Fvanishing-middle-class-struggling-opposition-productivism%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3Ehad%20earlier%20discussed%3C%2Fa%3E%20some%20of%20the%20growing%20concerns%20with%20India%20entering%20into%20a%20middle-income%20trap%20while%20witnessing%20a%20deep%2C%20gradual%20erosion%20of%20the%20promise%20of%20upward%20income%20mobility%20for%20its%20broader%20middle-income%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20expectations%2C%20salaried%20individuals%20may%20expect%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20basic%20exemption%20limit%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fbudget%2Fexpectations%2Fbudget-2024-pre-budget-expectations-for-salaried-individuals-on-income-tax-relief-11704784990018.html%5C%22%3Ehigher%20HRA%20(House%20Rent%20Allowance)%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20both%20the%20old%20and%20new%20tax%20regimes%20that%20can%20offer%20troubled%20middle%20income%20classes%20some%20relief%20against%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthree-charts-what-really-matters-to-india-versus-what-parties-jockey-for-in-emotional-tug-to-voters-hearts%5C%22%3Egrowing%20burdens%20of%20inflationary%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20period%20of%20stagnating%20real%20wages%20and%20joblessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20salaried%20classes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthree-charts-what-really-matters-to-india-versus-what-parties-jockey-for-in-emotional-tug-to-voters-hearts%5C%22%3Ehaven%E2%80%99t%20seen%20a%20substantive%20rise%20in%20incomes%3C%2Fa%3E%20(across%20both%20urban%20and%20rural%20areas)%20over%20the%20last%20seven%20years%20even%20though%20prices%20of%20essential%20consumer%20and%20capital%20goods%20have%20continued%20to%20rise.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fauthor%2F310387%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3Evalue%20of%20the%20rupee%20has%20considerably%20fallen%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20time%20as%20prices%20of%20essentials%20have%20gone%20up%2C%20which%20has%20added%20to%20the%20fiscal%20purse%20of%20the%20average%20Indian%20household%2C%20contributing%20to%20greater%20than%2035%25%20household%20debt%20to%20GDP%20levels%20(see%20more%20on%20this%20issue%20discussed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Feconomy%2Fin-9-charts-indias-growing-debt-problem-has-crisis-like-symptoms%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20a%20scenario%2C%20for%20those%20coming%20as%20part%20of%20the%20direct%20income%20tax%20base%2C%20providing%20a%20larger%20fiscal%20relief%20may%20be%20desirable%20for%20the%20government.%20The%20previous%20year%E2%80%99s%20Union%20budget%20granted%20income%20tax%20rebates%20for%20individuals%20earning%20up%20to%20Rs%205%2C00%2C000%2C%20creating%20expectations%20among%20the%20lower%20income%20spectrum%2C%20who%20would%20anticipate%20similar%20rebates%20in%20the%20upcoming%20interim%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20also%20a%20pending%20demand%20to%20increase%20the%20standard%20deduction%20limit%20after%20it%20was%20made%20part%20of%20the%20new%20income%20tax%20regime%20in%202023.%20This%20might%20be%20a%20much-needed%20relief%20for%20the%20salaried%20class%20that%2C%20on%20class-based%20vote%20considerations%2C%20has%20formed%20the%20core%20voter%20base%20of%20for%20the%20Modi%20government%20in%20urban%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20this%2C%20salaried%20individuals%20who%20receive%20House%20Rent%20Allowance%20(HRA)%20as%20a%20component%20of%20their%20salary%20and%20are%20currently%20residing%20in%20rented%20accommodation%20are%20anticipating%20an%20upward%20revision%20in%20the%20existing%20HRA%20exemption%20limit%20under%20Section%2010(13A).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20may%20further%20see%20a%20possible%20extension%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20National%20Pension%20System%20(NPS)%20to%20the%20New%20Tax%20Regime.%20If%20one%20looks%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mercer.com%2Finsights%2Finvestments%2Fmarket-outlook-and-trends%2Fmercer-cfa-global-pension-index%2F%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Pension%20Index%20Rankings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20is%20observed%20that%20India%20has%20been%20poorly%20ranked%20across%20years%2C%20presenting%20a%20grim%20picture%20on%20the%20fiscal%20state%20of%20social%20security%20for%20its%20citizens%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20for%20dependents%20and%20economically%20vulnerable%20sections%20of%20the%20demographic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgainst%20the%20needs%20and%20wishes%20of%20the%20vulnerable%20sections%20and%20affected-middle%20income%20classes%20in%20multiple%20crises%20shocks%2C%20what%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20consistently%20done%20is%20followed%20a%20consistent%20fiscal%20policy%20of%20corporate%20friendly%20supply-side%20economics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20perhaps%20been%20no%20government%20in%20independent%20India%20that%20has%20so%20blatantly%20supported%20the%20elite%2C%20wealthy%20class%20during%20crises%20times%20with%20announcements%20on%20reductions%20in%20corporate%20tax%20rates%2C%20ad%20hoc%20aggressive%20push%20to%20promoting%20big%20capital%20manufacturing%20enterprises%2C%20with%20incentives%20for%20exports%20through%20%E2%80%9Ctax%20holidays%E2%80%9D%2C%20responsible%20for%20a%20K-shaped%20economic%20growth%20trajectory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20more%20can%20be%20on%20tax%20reform%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fvoices%2Fopinion%2Findias-tax-reforms-will-modi-govts-2023-budget-be-middle-class-friendly%5C%22%3Eargued%20earlier%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20a%20few%20tangible%20fiscal%20measures%2C%20say%20on%20the%20fiscal%20tax%20side%2C%20a%20reduction%20in%20consumer%20(indirect)%20taxes%20may%20also%20help%20in%20at%20least%20increasing%20the%20disposable%20income%20of%20most%20under%20the%20tax%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESlight%20tinkering%20with%20tax%20rates%20helps%20but%20more%20can%20be%20done%20to%20bring%20out%20the%20indirect%20tax%20cost%20burden%20on%20the%20low-income%20and%20middle%20class.%20It%20may%20also%20give%20a%20much-needed%20fiscal%20space%20for%20the%20low-income%20class%20to%20save-spend%20more%20on%20discretion%2C%20given%20how%20much%20this%20income%20group%20has%20struggled%20through%20subsequent%20cycles%20of%20high%20inflation%20and%20pandemic%20induced%20misery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20to%20create%20more%20fiscal%20space%20for%20enhanced%20social%20(and%20welfare)%20spending%2C%20the%20government%20could%20have%20introduced%20a%20more%20structural%2C%20%E2%80%98bold%E2%80%99%20tax%20proposal%20%E2%80%93%20as%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fvoices%2Fopinion%2Findias-tax-reforms-will-modi-govts-2023-budget-be-middle-class-friendly%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98consumption%20tax%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20the%20top%201%25%20wealth%20endowed%20consumption%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fvoices%2Fopinion%2Findias-tax-reforms-will-modi-govts-2023-budget-be-middle-class-friendly%5C%22%3Eexplained%20before%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20a%20tax%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20only%20needed%20for%20concerns%20of%20distributive%20equity%20(the%20rising%20gap%20between%20the%20rich%20and%20poor%20or%20the%20squeezing%20of%20the%20middle%20class)%20but%20more%20importantly%2C%20this%20would%20have%20given%20the%20government%20more%20fiscal%20revenue%20options%20on%20the%20direct%20tax%20end%2C%20subsequently%20reducing%20its%20%E2%80%98spending-dependence%E2%80%99%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fvoices%2Fopinion%2Findias-tax-reforms-will-modi-govts-2023-budget-be-middle-class-friendly%5C%22%3Eincreased%20government%20borrowing%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(which%20has%20been%20very%20high).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20some%20of%20the%20other%20key%20macro-overheads%20reflecting%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20fiscal%20outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20backstory%20on%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20failed%20attempt%20at%20driving%20private%20investment%20for%20growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20present%20government%20has%20prioritised%20capital%20expenditure%2C%20with%20the%20CAPEX%20rising%20on%20a%20year-on-year%20basis%2C%20with%20a%20growth%20of%2028.57%25%20from%202022-23%20to%202023-24.%20Further%20studies%20by%20organisations%20like%20Crisil%20and%20Jefferies%20predict%20that%20CAPEX%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20GDP%20will%20reach%20nearly%2030%25%20in%20FY24%2C%20a%20decade-high%2C%20that%20will%20aid%20India%E2%80%99s%20resilience%20against%20a%20potential%20global%20slowdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fbudget-2023-is-optimistic-but-indifferent-to-past-failures%5C%22%3ECapex-fuelled%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20yielded%20no%20positive%20dividends%20in%20boosting%20domestic%20private%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20590px)%2085vw%2C%20590px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29155818%2FB1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22590%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29155818%2FB1.png%20590w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29155818%2FB1-300x175.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694808%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22344%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20CNES-InfoSphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%20has%20consistently%20exceeded%20its%20budgeted%20Capex%20targets%20in%20recent%20years.%20In%20FY22-23%2C%20the%20government%20expended%20Rs%207.36%20lakh%20crore%20compared%20to%20the%20revised%20estimate%20of%20Rs%207.28%20lakh%20crore.%20And%20for%20FY24%2C%20it%20has%20already%20crossed%20the%2050%25%20mark%20of%20the%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20crore%20that%20was%20announced%20in%20the%20budget.%20On%20FDI%2C%20the%20total%20foreign%20direct%20investment%20inflow%20into%20India%20dropped%20to%20%2470.9%20billion%20in%20the%20financial%20year%202023.%20There%20was%20a%2016%25%20decline%20from%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29155921%2FB2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22698%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29155921%2FB2.png%20698w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29155921%2FB2-300x185.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694809%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22430%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20CNES-InfoSphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20government%20capex%2C%20the%20government%20has%20aimed%20to%20spent%20roughly%20Rs%2010%20trillion%20on%20longer%20term%20capital%20expenditure%20for%202023-24%2C%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20enabling%20a%20growth-push%20objective.%20The%20last%20allocation%2C%20announced%20for%20FY23%20budget%2C%20was%20higher%20than%20the%20Rs%207.5%20trillion%20budgeted%20for%20in%20the%20previous%20year%20and%20the%20highest%20on%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20year-on-year%20increase%20of%2033%25%20is%20only%20marginally%20lower%20than%20FY22%E2%80%99s%2035%25%20jump.%20The%20ratio%20of%20capex-to-GDP%2C%20which%20rose%20to%202.7%25%20in%202022-23%2C%20was%20estimated%20at%203.3%25%20in%20FY23%2C%20as%20Sithar