271.html%5C%22%3Eargued%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Ehow%20vital%20this%20Budget%20was%20for%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20effort%20to%20intervene%20on%20the%20crisis%20of%20joblessness%20gripping%20across%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20finance%20minister%2C%20much%20like%20what%20she%20has%20done%20in%20the%20past%20four%20to%20five%20budget%20speeches%2C%20failed%20to%20mention%2Facknowledge%20the%20job%20creation%20crisis%20ripping%20through%20sectors%20across%20India.%20Token%20announcements%2C%20like%20every%20year%2C%20were%20made%20with%20limited%20effect%20on%20ensuring%20good%2C%20decent%20jobs%20for%20the%20young.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20effort%20to%20ensure%20upward%20social%20and%20income%20mobility%20amongst%20the%20youth%20is%20centred%20largely%20on%20establishing%20skill%20centres%20for%20international%20outreach%2C%20then%20we%20might%20sit%20on%20the%20largest%20%E2%80%98brain%20drain%E2%80%99%20of%20educated%2C%20young%20Indian%20aspirants%20abroad%20than%20ever%20seen%20before.%20Allocative%20outlays%20for%20targeted%20job%20creation%20across%20sectors%20has%20been%20avoided%20by%20past%20and%20current%20budgets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20providing%20job%20security%2C%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2Fjan%2F29%2Fneed-to-pivot-fiscal-policy-towards-job-creation-2542271.html%5C%22%3Eurban%20version%20of%20the%20MGNREGA%20programme%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20has%20been%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20for%20quite%20some%20time%20and%20advocated%20for%20by%20many%20policy%20economists%2C%20failed%20to%20receive%20any%20attention%20or%20mention.%20Even%20MGNREGA%E2%80%99s%20own%20allocation%20for%20this%20year%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fnrega-budget-allocation-2023-24%5C%22%3Eannounced%20at%20Rs%2060%2C000%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20the%20lowest%20made%20in%20comparison%20to%20what%20was%20announced%20in%20all%20of%20previous%20years%20during%20this%20term%20of%20the%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20retrospect%2C%2010%20years%20of%20Modi%20Government%E2%80%99s%20failed%20supply%20side%20interventions%20have%20led%20to%20%E2%80%98no%20gain%E2%80%99%20in%20creating%20good%20employment%20opportunities%20for%20the%20young%20-at%20a%20time%20when%20India%E2%80%99s%20demographic%20potential%20has%20been%20on%20a%20sweet%20spot%2C%20or%2C%20in%20driving%20private%20investment%20opportunities%20(despite%20all%20the%20fiscal%20carrots%20provided)%2C%20while%20barely%20spending%20on%20key%20social-welfare%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20interim%20budget%20may%20do%20very%20little%20to%20band-aid%20these%20structural%20concerns%20even%20if%20some%20soaps%20and%20candies%20maybe%20anticipated%20in%20the%20Government%E2%80%99s%20projected%20fiscal%20outlay%20announcement%20and%20vision%20before%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20Elections.%20What%E2%80%99s%20needed%20amidst%20all%20the%20noise%20created%20over%20the%20next%20week%20is%20a%20careful%20review%20of%20the%20final%20details%20that%20lie%20in%20the%20published%20budget%20documents%20as%20against%20any%20rhetorical%20speech%20that%20the%20finance%20minister%20may%20give.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20part%20of%20data-based%20explainers%20undertaken%20every%20year%20in%20a%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2Four-work%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Epre%20and%20post%20budget%20analysis%20by%20the%20InfoSphere%20team%20of%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20Team%20Credits%3A%20Amisha%20Singh%2C%20Aditi%20Desai%2C%20Aryan%20Govindkrishnan%2C%20Aman%20Chain%2C%20Jheel%20Doshi.%20For%20reviewing%20Team%20InfoSphere%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20please%20see%20its%20website%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706529605000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29162104%2Fkelly-sikkema-SBxdMoOY9zM-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-the-interim-union-budget-might-bring-and-the-context-in-which-to-judge-it%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%E2%80%99s%20needed%20amidst%20all%20the%20noise%20created%20over%20the%20next%20week%20is%20a%20careful%20review%20of%20the%20final%20details%20that%20lie%20in%20the%20published%20budget%20documents%20as%20against%20any%20rhetorical%20speech%20that%20the%20finance%20minister%20may%20give.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-the-interim-union-budget-might-bring-and-the-context-in-which-to-judge-it%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Understanding%20India's%20Interests%20in%20Myanmar's%20Paletwa%20That%20Pro-Democracy%20Forces%20Snatched%20from%20Junta%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29161008%2FEffect-89.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Continuing%20its%20victory%20march%20into%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20Junta-controlled%20areas%2C%20the%20pro-democracy%20armed%20forces%20of%20that%20country%20have%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irrawaddy.com%2Fnews%2Fwar-against-the-junta%2Farakan-army-declares-victory-in-paletwa-myanmars-chin-state.html%5C%22%3Esnatched%20control%20of%20Paletwa%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20a%20strategically%20key%20township%20in%20its%20Chin%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fall%20of%20Paletwa%20to%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20Rakhine-based%20ethnic%20armed%20organisation%20(EAO)%2C%20the%20Arakan%20Army%20(AA)%2C%20on%20January%2015%20came%20after%20two%20months%20of%20Junta%20resisting%20its%20seize.%20AA%20is%20one%20of%20the%20three%20militias%20to%20have%20joined%20hands%20with%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Defence%20Force%20(PDF)%2C%20the%20armed%20wing%20of%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20National%20Unity%20Government%20(NUG)%20in%20exile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20Paletwa%20borders%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20Chittagong%20Hill%20Tracts%20may%20have%20prompted%20the%20Bangladesh%20Border%20Guard%20(BBG)%20chief%20AKM%20Nazmul%20Hassan%20to%20at%20once%20dash%20off%20to%20that%20border%20to%20scrutinise%20its%20security%20preparations%20against%20infiltration%2C%20but%20that%20takeover%20of%20AA%20has%20much%20more%20strategic%20significance%20to%20India%20%E2%80%93%20more%20emphatically%20to%20Northeast%20India%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20its%20security%2C%20and%20also%20the%20expansion%20of%20trade%20and%20commerce%20from%2Fin%20that%20landlocked%20belt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPaletwa%E2%80%99s%20significance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPaletwa%2C%20positioned%20about%2020%20kms%20from%20the%20Bangladesh%20border%2C%20is%20a%20vital%20cog%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20Look%2FAct%20East%20Policy%2C%20more%20specifically%20to%20the%20India-funded%20multi-crore%20infrastructure%20venture%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Kaladan%20Road%20Project%2C%20or%20the%20Kaladan%20Multi-Model%20Transit%20Transport%20Project%2C%20started%20by%20the%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20(UPA)%20government%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20part%20of%20the%20ambitious%20bilateral%20project%2C%20estimated%20to%20be%20about%20Rs%203%2C200%20crore%20now%2C%20is%20to%20connect%20the%20Kolkata%20port%20at%20Hoogly%20to%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20Sittwe%20port.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20port%2C%20based%20in%20Sittwe%2C%20the%20capital%20of%20the%20Rakhine%20state%2C%20is%20on%20an%20estuarial%20patch%20shaped%20by%20the%20Kaladan%20River%20while%20joining%20two%20other%20rivers%20to%20empty%20into%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29161751%2F1200px-Kaladan_Multi-Modal_Transit_Transport_Project.svg_.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29161751%2F1200px-Kaladan_Multi-Modal_Transit_Transport_Project.svg_.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29161751%2F1200px-Kaladan_Multi-Modal_Transit_Transport_Project.svg_-300x176.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29161751%2F1200px-Kaladan_Multi-Modal_Transit_Transport_Project.svg_-1024x599.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29161751%2F1200px-Kaladan_Multi-Modal_Transit_Transport_Project.svg_-425x250.png%20425w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694821%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22702%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKaladan%20Multi-Modal%20Transit%20Transport%20Project.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FRaviC%2FCC%20BY-SA%204.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20linking%20of%20the%20seaports%20of%20Kolkata%20and%20Sittwe%20would%20give%20Myanmar%20a%20functional%20sea%20network%20with%20India%20and%20thereby%20boost%20bilateral%20trade%2C%20further%20expansion%20of%20the%20infrastructure%20project%20into%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20Chin%20State%20would%20go%20on%20to%20benefit%20India%20even%20more%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20blueprint%2C%20the%20project%20would%20link%20the%20Sittwe%20port%20in%20Rakhine%20State%20to%20the%20neighbouring%20Chin%20state%20through%20a%20river%20link%20on%20the%20Kaladan.%20Chin%20State%20borders%20Mizoram.%20The%20inland%20waterways%20would%20then%20reach%20Paletwa%20in%20Chin%20State.%20Thereafter%2C%20goods%20ferried%20from%20Kolkata%20to%20Sittwe%20to%20Paletwa%20by%20waterways%20would%20cross%20over%20to%20India%20through%20Mizoram%20by%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20completed%2C%20the%20Kaladan%20project%20would%20not%20only%20link%20a%20land-locked%20Northeast%20India%20to%20the%20sea%20through%20Sittwe%2C%20and%20also%20lessen%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20distance%20(currently%20only%20by%20road)%20to%20the%20Kolkata%20port%2C%20but%20also%20generate%20an%20alternate%20route%20to%20the%20region%20aside%20from%20the%20strategically%20vulnerable%20Siliguri%20Corridor%2C%20or%20what%20is%20commonly%20called%20the%20Chicken%E2%80%99s%20Neck.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20along%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20ongoing%20railway%20project%20with%20Bangladesh%20to%20join%20South%20Tripura%20with%20Chittagong%E2%80%99s%20Cox%E2%80%99s%20Bazar%20where%20a%20deep%20sea%20port%20is%20under%20construction%20(Cox%E2%80%99s%20Bazar%20also%20has%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20longest%20unbroken%20sea%20beach)%2C%20have%20been%20the%20ambitious%20ventures%20to%20help%20deliver%20to%20the%20northeastern%20states%20a%20window%20to%20the%20sea.%20Such%20a%20link%20would%20help%20open%20the%20resource-rich%20Northeastern%20expanse%20to%20wider%20commerce%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20linking%20Agartala%20with%20Kolkata%20through%20the%20Akhaura%20railway%20line%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20which%20is%20nearing%20completion%2C%20would%20further%20add%20to%20the%20warren%20of%20alternate%20routes%20to%20and%20from%20the%20Northeastern%20borderlands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20operational%20Sittwe%20port%20in%20Myanmar%20augurs%20well%20for%20Bangladesh%20too%20as%20its%20Teknaf%20Port%20is%20just%2060%20nautical%20miles%20away.%20Furthermore%2C%20goods%20from%20Kolkata%20can%20also%20be%20routed%20through%20Teknaf%20to%20reach%20Sabroom%2C%20located%20about%20300%20kms%20by%20road.%20Sabroom%20is%20in%20Tripura%20and%20has%20an%20integrated%20customs%20facility%2C%20or%20a%20land%20port.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Maitri%20Setu%2C%20or%20the%20friendship%20bridge%20over%20River%20Feni%20funded%20by%20India%2C%20is%20to%20connect%20this%20significant%20border%20town%20of%20Sabroom%20to%20Ramgarh%20in%20Chittagong.%20According%20to%20Land%20Ports%20Authority%20of%20India%20chairman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fagartala%2Findo-bangladesh-connectivity-via-tripuras-maitri-setu-likely-to-begin-in-feb-lpai-chairman%2Farticleshow%2F107114528.cms%5C%22%3EAditya%20Mishra%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20January%2024%2C%20the%20bridge%20would%20be%20operational%20this%20February%20%E2%80%93%E2%80%93%20three%20years%20after%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20%E2%80%98inaugurated%E2%80%99%20it%20virtually.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProgress%20in%20Kaladan%20Project%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20past%20May%2C%20minus%20much%20media%20glare%2C%20union%20ports%2C%20shipping%20and%20waterways%20minister%20and%20former%20Assam%20chief%20minister%2C%20Sarbananda%20Sonowal%2C%20travelled%20to%20his%20home%20town%20Dibrugarh%20in%20Assam%20to%20virtually%20receive%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1922176%5C%22%3Efirst%20Indian%20cargo%20ship%20sailing%20from%20Kolkata%20docking%20at%20the%20Sittwe%20Port%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20May%209%2C%202023%2C%20event%20was%20to%20declare%20the%20Kolkata%20to%20Sittwe%20slice%20of%20the%20Kaladan%20project%20operational.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20Indian%20side%2C%20as%20per%20the%20official%20record%2C%20the%20road%20component%20of%20the%20Kaladan%20project%20is%20also%20nearly%20complete.%20In%20April%202023%2C%20the%20Mizoram%20government%E2%80%99s%20Public%20Works%20Department%20led%20by%20chief%20engineer%20C.%20Lalchhuana%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finfra.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Froads-highways%2F98pc-of-cross-border-road-under-kaladan-project-completed-in-mizoram-official%2F99309957%5C%22%3Ehad%20informed%3C%2Fa%3E%20state%20governor%20Haribabu%20Kambhampati%20that%20%E2%80%9C98.01%25%20of%20the%20road%20component%20of%20the%20Kaladan%20project%20on%20the%20Mizoram%20side%20(national%20highway%20501A)%20has%20been%20completed%20so%20far.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECorrespondingly%2C%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20commerce%20minister%20U.%20Aung%20Naing%20Oo%20had%20also%20announced%20in%20June%20last%20year%20that%20the%20road%20to%20connect%20Paletwa%20with%20the%20border%20town%20of%20Zorinpui%20in%20Mizoram%20%E2%80%9Cis%20underway%20in%20full%20swing%E2%80%9D.%20Though%20the%20Indian%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20external%20affairs%20R.%20K.%20Ranjan%20Singh%2C%20an%20MP%20from%20Manipur%20which%20also%20shares%20a%20long%20border%20with%20Myanmar%2C%20had%20told%20reporters%20in%20March%20last%20year%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20unpredictable%20atmosphere%20occurring%20in%20Myanmar%E2%80%9D%20has%20affected%20the%20progress%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finfra.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fports-shipping%2Fconstruction-of-road-on-myanmar-side-in-full-swing-says-minister%2F100959017%5C%22%3EKaladan%20project%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20the%20Myanmarese%20commerce%20minister%20and%20Junta%20leader%2C%20two%20months%20later%20had%2C%20however%2C%20dismissed%20the%20anti-Junta%20combats%20in%20the%20region%20having%20any%20effect%20on%20infrastructure%20linking%20with%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20past%20January%2015%20though%2C%20the%20field%20situation%20seemed%20to%20have%20undergone%20a%20paradigm%20shift%20with%20AA%20taking%20over%20Paletwa%2C%20forcing%20the%20Junta%20to%20surrender%20all%2024%20of%20its%20positions%20in%20that%20area%2C%20including%20the%20Light%20Infantry%20Battalion%20289%20headquarters%20from%20where%20its%20brigadier%20generals%20had%20controlled%20the%20township.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20AA%20control%20of%20Paletwa%20is%20bad%20news%20for%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20Brotherhood%20Alliance%2C%20stitched%20between%20NUG%E2%80%99s%20armed%20wing%2C%20the%20PDF%2C%20and%20the%20three%20powerful%20EAOs%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0the%20AA%2C%20the%20Myanmar%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20Army%20(MNDAA)%20and%20the%20Ta%E2%80%99ang%20National%20Liberation%20Army%20(TNLA)%20%E2%80%93%20operations%20to%20weed%20out%20Junta%20began%20close%20to%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20international%20borders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20this%20past%20October%2C%20the%20Alliance%20forces%2C%20under%20Operation%201027%2C%20have%20been%20able%20to%20wrest%20control%20of%20several%20strategic%20townships%20close%20to%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20borders%20with%20India%2C%20China%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20Thailand%2C%20pushing%20thousands%20of%20refugees%20to%20flee%20to%20neighbouring%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20January%2015%20takeover%20of%20Paletwa%20by%20AA%20is%20part%20of%20that%20victory%20curve.%20Since%20Paletwa%20is%20a%20crucial%20component%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20infrastructure%20development%20in%20eastern%20and%20north-eastern%20India%2C%20a%20region%20hemmed%20in%20by%20China%2C%20it%20becomes%20vital%20then%20to%20put%20a%20close%20lens%20on%20the%20Arakan%20Army%3B%20importantly%2C%20its%20approach%20towards%20China%20and%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%202009%20to%20establish%20an%20%E2%80%98Arakan%20nation%E2%80%99%2C%20AA%20today%20has%20grown%20to%20a%20strength%20of%20over%20thirty%20thousand%20soldiers.%20AA%20was%20formed%20with%20help%20from%20the%20Kachin%20Independence%20Army%2C%20one%20of%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20most%20powerful%20groups%20which%20is%20also%20believed%20to%20have%20trained%20militants%20from%20Northeast%20India%20in%20the%201980s-90s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20AA%20is%20Rakhine-based%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stimson.org%2F2023%2Funderstanding-the-arakan-army%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Washington-based%20think%20tank%2C%20the%20Stimson%20Center%2C%20had%20stated%20this%20past%20April%20that%20%E2%80%9Cat%20least%206%2C000%20troops%20are%20stationed%20in%20areas%20controlled%20by%20AA%20allies%2C%20such%20as%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20north%20and%20northeast.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20incisive%20report%20by%20Kyaw%20Hsan%20Hlaing%2C%20a%20noted%20Myanmar%20observer%2C%20it%20goes%20on%20to%20underline%20the%20reasons%20why%20AA%20has%20grown%20so%20phenomenally%20in%20spite%20of%20being%20one%20of%20the%20youngest%20EAOs%20in%20Myanmar.%20Importantly%2C%20AA%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Federal%20Political%20Negotiation%20and%20Coordination%20Committee%2C%20a%20coalition%20spearheaded%20by%20the%20United%20Wa%20State%20Army%20(UWSA)%2C%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20largest%20and%20strongest%20group%20which%20runs%20the%20autonomous%20Wa%20State.%20UWSA%20is%20a%20strong%20ally%20of%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20time%20to%20time%2C%20some%20observers%20have%20also%20published%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-supplying-weapons-to-arakan-army-armed-group-to-weaken-india-myanmar-report%2Farticleshow%2F76741890.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20China%20funding%20AA%20to%20have%20leverage%20over%20Myanmar%20and%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20AA%20has%20earlier%20attacked%20the%20India-backed%20Kaladan%20project%20but%20has%20never%20touched%20any%20Chinese%20big-ticket%20infrastructure%20projects%20in%20the%20region%20is%20also%20oft-cited%20as%20proof%20of%20AA%E2%80%99s%20proximity%20to%20China%20and%20its%20geopolitical%20interests.%20In%20early%202019%2C%20India%20and%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20military%20is%20understood%20to%20have%20launched%20a%20joint%20operation%20to%20chase%20away%20the%20AA%20forces%20obstructing%20the%20Kaladan%20project.%20In%20retaliation%2C%20AA%20had%20abducted%20five%20Indians%20working%20at%20the%20Kaladan%20site%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Findian-worker-part-of-kaladan-project-dies-in-custody-of-myanmar-insurgent-group-1615819-2019-11-05%5C%22%3Edeath%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20one.%20In%20mid-2020%20too%2C%20there%20was%20a%20face-off%20between%20AA%20and%20Junta%20forces%20close%20to%20the%20project%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20past%20January%2C%20with%20Junta%2C%20supporting%20the%20project%2C%20and%20surrendering%20control%20of%20Paletwa%20to%20AA%2C%20seen%20close%20to%20China%2C%20the%20completion%20of%20the%20crucial%20venture%20is%20certainly%20under%20a%20cloud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChinese%20infrastructure%20projects%20in%20the%20region%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20India%20creating%20a%20trade%20corridor%20with%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20Rakhine%20State%20through%20Sittwe%2C%20China%20is%20funding%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mizzima.com%2Fbusiness-domestic%2Fparliament-passes-first-phase-kyaukphyu-sez%5C%22%3EKyaukphyu%20Special%20Economic%20Zone%3C%2Fa%3E%20(SEZ)%20in%20that%20state%20to%20also%20craft%20its%20business%20interest%20and%20to%20uplift%20its%20backward%20Yunnan%20Province.%20The%20SEZ%20will%20be%20linked%20to%20the%20Shwe%20Gas%20Field%20through%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20to%20Yunnan.%20China%20is%20also%20linking%20that%20part%20of%20its%20country%20with%20Myanmar%20through%20a%20railway%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20tandem%2C%20India%20has%20also%20recently%20announced%20financing%20a%20railway%20line%20between%20the%20Chin%20State%20and%20Mizoram.%20Huge%20infrastructure%20investment%20by%20India%20in%20the%20western%20part%20of%20Myanmar%20touching%20Northeast%20India%20is%20also%20because%20it%20is%20not%20only%20the%20gateway%20to%20ASEAN%20but%20also%20to%20likely%20counter%20China%E2%80%99s%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20then%20that%20China%20increasingly%20being%20seen%20backing%20the%20EAOs%20to%20take%20control%20of%20the%20border%20areas%20is%20a%20worrying%20development.%20The%20continuous%20capture%20of%20key%20towns%20by%20the%20EAOs%20bordering%20India%20including%20Paletwa%2C%20has%2C%20therefore%2C%20only%20bared%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20shadow%20of%20the%20civil%20war%20in%20Myanmar%20can%20only%20grow%20over%20India%E2%80%99s%20Northeast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20NUG%20government%20in%20exile%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Findia-psu-bel-arms-myanmar-export%5C%22%3Edispleasure%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20for%20some%20time%20now%20for%20having%20backed%20the%20Junta%20diplomatically%20and%20with%20the%20supply%20of%20arms%2C%20and%20the%20Manipur%20ethnic%20conflict%20close%20to%20the%20Myanmar%20border%20nowhere%20near%20an%20end%20further%20adds%20to%20the%20intricacies%20of%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20geopolitik.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706527811000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29161008%2FEffect-89.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Funderstanding-indias-interests-in-myanmars-paletwa-that-pro-democracy-forces-snatched-from-junta%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20fall%20of%20Junta-controlled%20key%20township%20into%20hands%20of%20Arakan%20Army%20holds%20significance%20for%20India's%20Look%2FAct%20East%20policy%2C%20particularly%20to%20the%20India-funded%20Kaladan%20Road%20Project.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Funderstanding-indias-interests-in-myanmars-paletwa-that-pro-democracy-forces-snatched-from-junta%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20are%20the%20Iran-backed%20militia%20groups%20carrying%20out%20attacks%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706527800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F1600x900%2Fskynews-iran-iraq_6436835.jpg%3F20240129105624%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwho-are-the-iran-backed-militia-groups-carrying-out-attacks-13059199%22%2C%